WEBVTT

00:01.177 --> 00:03.634
NATO is a child of the Cold War.

00:03.856 --> 00:07.707
When it was founded in 1949, there were 12 members.

00:08.003 --> 00:10.418
Today, the club has expanded to 30.

00:10.610 --> 00:13.625
Two in North America, 28 in Europe.

00:13.897 --> 00:17.191
NATO is built around the principle of collective defense...

00:17.405 --> 00:22.061
...which means an attack on one member is an attack on all of them.

00:22.439 --> 00:26.026
Their rival during the Cold War was the Warsaw Pact,...

00:26.205 --> 00:29.220
... a similar alliance led by the Soviet Union.

00:29.499 --> 00:32.451
Three NATO members are also nuclear powers.

00:32.626 --> 00:35.672
The US, UK, and France.

00:35.815 --> 00:40.688
Together, NATO makes up around 57 percent of global military spending.

00:40.921 --> 00:46.765
The United States is the undeclared leader providing 22 percent of the alliance's budget.

00:47.029 --> 00:49.796
NATO's power center is in Brussels.

